cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic video analysis tasks such as human action recognition and multi-person pose estimation. It also proposes a novel recurrent architecture to deal with multiple input sources. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and proposes a new training strategy, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper deals with video analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a new architecture for learning reciprocal feature representations, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
